The University of Kent, United Kingdom has given Afrobeats songstress an honorary doctorate degree in music. The UK varsity on July 5 announced its intention to honour some of its alumni, including Tiwa Savage, who graduated with a degree in Business Administration for her outstanding and inspirational performances in the music industry.   My battle with sickle cell, by Adekunle Gold     Asake for maiden SPOB jive     Baba Ijesha: Yomi Fabiyi’s estranged lover cancels…   The award-winning singer was awarded “Doctor in Music” with the varsity sharing the picture of the event, which took place at the Canterbury Cathedral on its Twitter handle. “Congratulations Dr @TiwaSavage! We’re super proud to have awarded the Queen of Afrobeats an honorary doctorate at Canterbury Cathedral this morning. #MadeInKent #KentGrads,” the university tweeted.